Step 2: Calculate the missing percentage of each column using a function. If any column has missing data more than 5%, please remove it. (Do not try this for rows) Define function:

missing_percent<-function(x)
{
  (sum(is.na(x))/length(x))*100
}

missing_col_percent <- apply(Covid19_df,2,missing_percent)
